      "content": "Even though you're feeling nauseous and reluctant to seek hospital care, your symptoms alone—chest tightness and a dull ache in your left arm—warrant immediate attention. A dull ache can still be serious and aspirin itself doesn't solve the underlying issue that could be causing your pain. I cannot stress enough the importance of getting help. There is a risk of severe complications, like a heart attack, if left unchecked. It's essential to get assessed by a medical professional to determine the correct and safe course of action. Do your best to find someone to drive you, call an ambulance, or visit an urgent care clinic while you're feeling this way. It's better to be safe than sorry.",
